						<h3>Can varicose veins be cured without surgery?</h3>
						<figure>
							<img src="./img/image00163.jpg" alt="">
						</figure>
						 <strong>Can varicose veins be cured without surgery?</strong><p><span>Many people are concerned </span><span><b>about whether varicose veins can be treated without surgery</b></span><span>?</span></p><p><span>At first, varicose veins bring only heaviness in the legs, sometimes vascular asterisks and slightly dilated veins. But then the disease progresses, and in the last stages it is already present there are nutritional disorders of the leg tissues: ulcers, varicose spots and nodes, which can bring constant pain and heaviness, so that you want to get rid of it as soon as possible.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Characteristic signs of varicose veins: varicose nodes, dilated veins, pain and heaviness in the legs. A source images: xnog.ru</span></figcaption></figure><p><span>Many people constantly meet some rave reviews or, for example, ads for miracle ointments that promise to get rid of varicose veins forever. Let's find </span><span><i>out if varicose veins can be cured without surgery?</i></span></p><h2><span>Is it possible to treat varicose veins</span></h2><p><span>Varicosity — this is a chronic disease, and unfortunately, what the disease has done cannot be returned. Varicose veins can only be prevented. Even modern remedies can only stop the further development of varicose veins and ease the symptoms.</span></p><h2><span>What should I do so that I don't need an operation from varicose veins?</span></h2><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Compression knitwear is an excellent method for stopping and preventing varicose veins. varicube.ru</span></figcaption></figure><p><span>If you have the initial stages, and the nutrition of the leg tissues is not yet disturbed, then you can completely stop varicose veins. To do this, you must:</span></p><p><span>1. Software opportunities to change your occupation, change your lifestyle, engage in non-strenuous active sports in order to eliminate blood stasis. </span></p><p><span>2. Change your diet (</span><span></span><a><u><b>healthy foods</b></u></a><span> and </span><span></span><a><u><b>foods that need to be excluded</b></u></a><span>), get rid of excess weight (if it exists, then it only adds to the load on the legs).</span></p><p><span>3. Take prescribed medications and wear compression underwear.</span></p><h2><span>When without surgery for varicose veins can not do?</span></h2><ul><li><span>the disease progresses rapidly and nothing helps;</span></li><li><span>the patient experiences constant severe pain or is not happy the appearance of their feet;</span></li><li><span>with severe nutritional disorders of the leg tissues —long-lasting ulcers do not heal;</span></li><li><span>acute thrombophlebitis.</span></li></ul><p><span><b>But, it should be understood that the decision about the operation still remains with the doctor.</b></span></p><h2><span>How dangerous is varicose veins surgery</span></h2><p><span>Almost all operations for varicose veins they pass with success, only sometimes there are complications in the form of bruises, edema, bleeding.</span></p><p><span>Modern methods of treatment have been developed, in which the intervention is minimal, for example, removing vessels with a laser or sintering vessels with special substances or microwaves. The risk of complications with them is extremely low, especially varicose veins after them return much less often.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>Laser removal of varicose veins is a fairly common and non-traumatic operation. Image source: lechenieus-varikozus.ru</span></figcaption></figure><h2><span>How long does it take to recover from vein surgery</span></h2><p><span>Sometimes people do there are edema on the legs, fever increases for 2-3 days.</span></p><p><span>After surgery, there is a danger of blood clots, so doctors prescribe wearing bandages or compression underwear and doing simple exercises. For six months, you will not be able to lift weights.  </span></p><blockquote><span><i>If you think the article is useful, put </i></span><span><i><b>a like</b></i></span><span><i> and </i></span><span><i><b>subscribe</b></i></span><span><i> to the channel, so more people will see it.</i></span></blockquote><blockquote><span><i>The articles are informative and do not cancel a specialist's consultation!</i></span></blockquote><div></div>
